# Like / Dislike / Report Feature

Add like, dislike, and report buttons below each AI response (next to the existing Save to Note button). Include an admin page to view/filter all feedback.

## Proposed Changes

### Database Migration

#### [NEW] [19.surrealql](file:///d:/Project%20Web/open-notebook/open_notebook/database/migrations/19.surrealql)

Create `feedback` table:
- `feedback_type`: enum `like | dislike | report`
- `question`: the user's question (human message before this AI response)
- `answer`: the AI response content
- `report_content`: optional text (only for reports)
- [user_id](file:///d:/Project%20Web/open-notebook/open_notebook/domain/notebook.py#582-589): record reference to user
- Indexes on [user_id](file:///d:/Project%20Web/open-notebook/open_notebook/domain/notebook.py#582-589), `feedback_type`, `created`

#### [NEW] [19_down.surrealql](file:///d:/Project%20Web/open-notebook/open_notebook/database/migrations/19_down.surrealql)

`REMOVE TABLE feedback;`

---

### Backend Domain Model

#### [MODIFY] [notebook.py](file:///d:/Project%20Web/open-notebook/open_notebook/domain/notebook.py)

Add `Feedback` class extending [ObjectModel](file:///d:/Project%20Web/open-notebook/open_notebook/domain/base.py#31-208):
```python
class Feedback(ObjectModel):
    table_name = "feedback"
    nullable_fields = {"report_content", "user_id"}
    record_fields = {"user_id"}
    feedback_type: Literal["like", "dislike", "report"]
    question: str
    answer: str
    report_content: Optional[str] = None
    user_id: Optional[str] = None
```

---

### Backend API Models

#### [MODIFY] [models.py](file:///d:/Project%20Web/open-notebook/api/models.py)

Add request/response models:
- `FeedbackCreate`: `feedback_type`, `question`, `answer`, `report_content` (optional)
- `FeedbackResponse`: all fields + [id](file:///d:/Project%20Web/open-notebook/open_notebook/domain/notebook.py#324-333), `created`, `updated`, `username`
- `FeedbackListResponse`: list wrapper with count

---

### Backend Router

#### [NEW] [feedback.py](file:///d:/Project%20Web/open-notebook/api/routers/feedback.py)

- `POST /feedback` — create feedback (any user)
- `GET /feedback` — list all feedback (admin only), with query params:
  - `feedback_type` filter (like/dislike/report)
  - `date_from` / `date_to` date filters
  - pagination (`page`, `page_size`)

#### [MODIFY] [main.py](file:///d:/Project%20Web/open-notebook/api/main.py)

Register the feedback router.

---

### Frontend – Chat Buttons

#### [MODIFY] [MessageActions.tsx](file:///d:/Project%20Web/open-notebook/frontend/src/components/source/MessageActions.tsx)

Add 3 new buttons after Save to Note:
- 👍 Like button (icon: `ThumbsUp`)
- 👎 Dislike button (icon: `ThumbsDown`)
- 🚩 Report button (icon: `Flag`) — opens a dialog

The [MessageActions](file:///d:/Project%20Web/open-notebook/frontend/src/components/source/MessageActions.tsx#16-120) component will receive an additional `question` prop (the preceding human message).

#### [MODIFY] [ChatPanel.tsx](file:///d:/Project%20Web/open-notebook/frontend/src/components/source/ChatPanel.tsx)

Pass the preceding human message's content as `question` prop to [MessageActions](file:///d:/Project%20Web/open-notebook/frontend/src/components/source/MessageActions.tsx#16-120).

